The leadership of the Asiwaju Ahmed Tinubu Support Group (AATSG) has visited the former Inspector General of Police (IGP), Dr Mike Okiro. The visit formed part of the group’s nationwide mobilisation for the actualisation of Tinubu’s dream for the 2023 presidential ticket of the All Progressives Congress (APC). The visit led by the National Leader of the AATSG, Otunba Abayomi Odunowo, had in attendance the group’s National Publicity Secretary, Hon. Sam Atasia Oburu, Deputy National Woman Leader, Zara, and Legal Adviser, Madam Okpala. Otunba Odunowo and his entourage were received by the former IGP, Mr Mike Okiro who intimated to his host about the mission of the group and Tinubu’s desire to emerge as the APC’s flag bearer and Nigerian president in the 2023 elections. He described Tinubu as a visionary leader endowed with everything necessary to govern the country, saying his experiences in the corporate world and politics stood him in good stead to steer the ship of the country on the path to global reckoning. Odunowo commended Okiro’s acceptance of the offer as the Zonal Patron of the group. He assured his host of the resolve and commitment of Asiwaju Tinubu for a change in the project called Nigeria.He described Tinubu as the most experienced and qualified to take over the mantle of leadership from President Mohammadu Buhari come 2023. In his response, Okiro lauded the effort of the group in reaching out to others across the country. POLL He said the Asiwaju Ahmed Tinubu was not new to him as a former super cop policeman of note. He announced an acceptance of the offer by the Asiwaju Ahmed Tinubu Support Group as its patron for the South East region.